Today's update includes the following activities:

1. Gravel installation is scheduled for tomorrow, as mentioned by Ron Heller.
2. Aaron Wilson reported that the material for the sliding door hardware arrived today and will be shipped directly to the office.
3. Electrical trim work is planned to continue on Saturday and Monday.
4. Aaron Wilson is following up on a garage door quote and selections.
5. Countertop templating is scheduled for Friday, including the backsplash.

These updates were shared by Aaron Wilson and Ron Heller on April 24, 2025.

Yesterday, several activities were happening at the 1320 Mayfair project site. The drywall team was working on sanding and finishing any imperfections in the ceiling, with Gerardo and Alex present on-site. Additionally, pavers were being delivered, and there were preparations for gravel installation scheduled for today. Ron Heller mentioned that the front yard was backfilled and graded, with tree protection and mulch sock being set up. He also noted that gravel installation was planned for today, and the paver installation would start next week. Aaron Wilson confirmed that electrical trim work would continue on Saturday and Monday, and he was following up on the garage door quote and selections. Furthermore, material for the sliding door hardware arrived and was being shipped to the office. Aaron also mentioned that templating for countertops and backsplash was scheduled for Friday. 

This summary is based on messages from Aaron Wilson and Ron Heller on April 28, 2025.

Today, the drywall team is working on sanding and finishing any imperfections in the ceiling. Gerardo and Alex are on site, and pavers are being delivered. Additionally, backfilling and grading of the front yard are in progress, with tree saving and mulch sock installation underway.
